<font style="font-size:10"><A href="http://www.andreasen.org/bartle/test.cgi">Explorer-66% Killer-60% Socializer-46% Achiever-26%</A></font></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#DEEFDE><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub18.ezboard.com/ulillywhite.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Lillywhite</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>MithMarr Squire</span><br>  Posts: 28<br> <font color=#006400>(2/12/02 8:35:28 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub18.ezboard.com/fmithanielmarrdailynewsfrm40.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=281.topic&index=41>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Lillywhite's Ragefire Rule</span><hr size=1> Hi Everyone!  Thanks for all your comments and thoughts.  <br>
<br>
Verant has made rules, but those rules are only invoked if somone petitions, leaving us free to change them, if we agree among ourselves to do so.  They want rules that are cost effictive as they can be while still being verifiable. I feel that verant would have no problems at all if we could find a better system than the one they have given us, such that the number of petitions and fights went down and saved them money.<br>
<br>
However, I suppose it is ironic, that even in a fantasy game one is sometimes forced to face reality.  You all make excellent points in arguing for reality, you have clearly previously considered the ideas I proposed, and have hit the same wall of reality before this, and so your advice is based upon experience of the dreams you lost in not being able to go over or around it.<br>
  <br>
As the new guild leader of Ancient Prophecy, I have been thinking about the type of guild we shall become, how we can be &quot;Honorable&quot;, what policies we should make that will guide our officers to treat the other guilds with the same respect we wish ourselves to be accorded when I am not on line to make a decision. Change needs to start someplace, or esle we loose hope that change is possible.<br>
<br>
I invite you all to visit our web page at <!--EZCODE AUTOLINK START--><a href="http://crystalimg.com/ancient-prophecy">crystalimg.com/ancient-prophecy</a><!--EZCODE AUTOLINK END--> where I will start a post in the general section to discuss what policies and ideals our guild, or any guild, should have.  I don't want us do become the topic of someone's &quot;Rant&quot; on this web page in the future as we grow larger, and I feel that by taking the time now to think about this, it will benefit everyone and perhaps provide a guild for other guilds who wish to change things for the better too, but can't find a way around....the Wall of Reality. Thanks!<br>
<br>
Lillywhite<br>
